"use strict";(self.webpackChunkcharlesancheta_com=self.webpackChunkcharlesancheta_com||[]).push([[1477],{10:function(e){e.exports=JSON.parse('{"blogPosts":[{"id":"dev-log/boboman/day4","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/dev-log/boboman/day4","editUrl":"https://github.com/cbebe/charlesancheta.com/edit/master/blog/dev-log/boboman/2022-07-06-day4/index.md","source":"@site/blog/dev-log/boboman/2022-07-06-day4/index.md","title":"Dev Log: Boboman - Day 4","description":"I feel like the hardest part of writing this game would be the enemy logic.","date":"2022-07-06T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"July 6, 2022","tags":[{"label":"dev-log","permalink":"/blog/tags/dev-log"},{"label":"love","permalink":"/blog/tags/love"},{"label":"lua","permalink":"/blog/tags/lua"},{"label":"multiplayer","permalink":"/blog/tags/multiplayer"}],"readingTime":0.385,"truncated":false,"authors":[{"name":"Charles Ancheta","title":"Computer Engineering Student","url":"https://github.com/cbebe","imageURL":"https://github.com/cbebe.png","key":"cbebe"}],"frontMatter":{"title":"Dev Log: Boboman - Day 4","authors":"cbebe","slug":"dev-log/boboman/day4","tags":["dev-log","love","lua","multiplayer"]},"nextItem":{"title":"Dev Log: Boboman - Day 3","permalink":"/blog/dev-log/boboman/day3"}},"content":"I feel like the hardest part of writing this game would be the enemy logic.\\nThat\'s why I\'m putting it off for as long as possible! Today I implemented map\\ngeneration, randomly placing boxes sufficiently far enough from players.\\n\\n![](./multiplayer.webp)\\n\\nI also added controls for other players, which reminded me of my local\\nmultiplayer experience with Boxhead. I miss having multiple people on play a\\nsingle keyboard. These days it would be awkward to play that way."},{"id":"dev-log/boboman/day3","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/dev-log/boboman/day3","editUrl":"https://github.com/cbebe/charlesancheta.com/edit/master/blog/dev-log/boboman/2022-07-05-day3.md","source":"@site/blog/dev-log/boboman/2022-07-05-day3.md","title":"Dev Log: Boboman - Day 3","description":"Feeling good today. I got to fix the collision bug that was happening","date":"2022-07-05T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"July 5, 2022","tags":[{"label":"dev-log","permalink":"/blog/tags/dev-log"},{"label":"love","permalink":"/blog/tags/love"},{"label":"lua","permalink":"/blog/tags/lua"}],"readingTime":0.685,"truncated":false,"authors":[{"name":"Charles Ancheta","title":"Computer Engineering Student","url":"https://github.com/cbebe","imageURL":"https://github.com/cbebe.png","key":"cbebe"}],"frontMatter":{"title":"Dev Log: Boboman - Day 3","authors":"cbebe","slug":"dev-log/boboman/day3","tags":["dev-log","love","lua"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Dev Log: Boboman - Day 4","permalink":"/blog/dev-log/boboman/day4"},"nextItem":{"title":"Dev Log: Boboman - Day 2","permalink":"/blog/dev-log/boboman/day2"}},"content":"Feeling good today. I got to fix the collision bug that was happening\\nyesterday. It actually had to do with the collision lifecycle, so to make the\\nplayer detectable, I decoupled the check from the lifecycle of the bomb.\\nBecause of this, I could revert the player\'s bomb timer to normal. Moving away\\nfrom a project and letting your brain sit on a problem for a while really does\\nwonders.\\n\\nI also created an enemy entity based off the player asset and make that and the\\nbox entities destructible by explosions. I thought I lost my commit progress on\\nit after mashing a few keys on `lazygit`, but I got it back after a `git\\nreflog` and `git cherry-pick` combo.\\n\\nOverall, I\'m making pretty good progress, and shaping the game more by adding\\nstuff to the TODO."},{"id":"dev-log/boboman/day2","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/dev-log/boboman/day2","editUrl":"https://github.com/cbebe/charlesancheta.com/edit/master/blog/dev-log/boboman/2022-07-04-day2.md","source":"@site/blog/dev-log/boboman/2022-07-04-day2.md","title":"Dev Log: Boboman - Day 2","description":"MAJOR BUG ALERT!!","date":"2022-07-04T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"July 4, 2022","tags":[{"label":"dev-log","permalink":"/blog/tags/dev-log"},{"label":"love","permalink":"/blog/tags/love"},{"label":"lua","permalink":"/blog/tags/lua"},{"label":"gh-pages","permalink":"/blog/tags/gh-pages"}],"readingTime":0.715,"truncated":false,"authors":[{"name":"Charles Ancheta","title":"Computer Engineering Student","url":"https://github.com/cbebe","imageURL":"https://github.com/cbebe.png","key":"cbebe"}],"frontMatter":{"title":"Dev Log: Boboman - Day 2","authors":"cbebe","slug":"dev-log/boboman/day2","tags":["dev-log","love","lua","gh-pages"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Dev Log: Boboman - Day 3","permalink":"/blog/dev-log/boboman/day3"},"nextItem":{"title":"Dev Log: Boboman - Day 1","permalink":"/blog/dev-log/boboman/day1"}},"content":"MAJOR BUG ALERT!!\\n\\nApparently my collision logic for the bombs weren\'t going to hold up. Every\\ntime a bomb explodes, there is a small time window where you can place a bomb\\nand the bomb would not recognize the player, making it a \\"not new\\" bomb.\\nBecause of that, the player gets pushed off right away and could end up in the\\nweirdest of places.\\n\\nAfter hours of debugging I couldn\'t really solve it because of how the\\ncollision library orders the entity updates. I didn\'t feel like giving up for\\ntoday, though, and making no progress. I simply created a deployment script to\\ndeploy the game to [GitHub pages](https://cbebe.github.io/boboman/) and fixed\\nthe player update logic so it at least doesn\'t end up outside of the map. Still\\na pretty good day even if I didn\'t make as much progress as I wanted."},{"id":"dev-log/boboman/day1","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/dev-log/boboman/day1","editUrl":"https://github.com/cbebe/charlesancheta.com/edit/master/blog/dev-log/boboman/2022-07-03-day1/index.md","source":"@site/blog/dev-log/boboman/2022-07-03-day1/index.md","title":"Dev Log: Boboman - Day 1","description":"Recently, I\'ve been heavily configuring my text editor, Neovim, which means","date":"2022-07-03T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"July 3, 2022","tags":[{"label":"dev-log","permalink":"/blog/tags/dev-log"},{"label":"love","permalink":"/blog/tags/love"},{"label":"lua","permalink":"/blog/tags/lua"}],"readingTime":0.97,"truncated":true,"authors":[{"name":"Charles Ancheta","title":"Computer Engineering Student","url":"https://github.com/cbebe","imageURL":"https://github.com/cbebe.png","key":"cbebe"}],"frontMatter":{"title":"Dev Log: Boboman - Day 1","authors":"cbebe","slug":"dev-log/boboman/day1","tags":["dev-log","love","lua"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Dev Log: Boboman - Day 2","permalink":"/blog/dev-log/boboman/day2"},"nextItem":{"title":"Bye bye Netlify","permalink":"/blog/bye-bye-netlify"}},"content":"Recently, I\'ve been heavily configuring my text editor, Neovim, which means\\nthat I\'ve been writing a lot of Lua. I do find it enjoyable, even without\\nhaving any tooling initially, so I wanted to give game development and\\n[Love2D](https://love2d.org) a try. I just finished [Sheepolution\'s How to\\nL\xd6VE](https://www.sheepolution.com/learn/book/contents) book on Love2D, and\\nfelt prepared to make my first game from scratch. As per Jherzey\'s request, I\'m\\ncreating a Bomberman clone.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\nI tried looking for libraries that might be useful at first, such as the ones\\nused in [Commando Kibbles](https://github.com/bakpakin/CommandoKibbles). I\\nwanted to set up an Entity-Component system and all those other fancy game dev\\nstuff I\'ve been hearing about. However, I realized that I should only use the\\nones that I don\'t feel like re-writing. After all, the prerequisite to writing\\ngood code is writing bad code. In the end, _Boboman_ seems like a fitting\\ntitle, because I do feel dumb writing this game.\\n\\nAnyway, here\'s what it looks like now. You can walk around, place bombs, and\\nthose bombs explode after a set amount of time, leaving a trail of explosion.\\nThe explosions don\'t go past the walls.\\n\\n![Boboman Day 1 demo](./boboman.gif)"},{"id":"bye-bye-netlify","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/bye-bye-netlify","editUrl":"https://github.com/cbebe/charlesancheta.com/edit/master/blog/2022-06-19-bye-bye-netlify.md","source":"@site/blog/2022-06-19-bye-bye-netlify.md","title":"Bye bye Netlify","description":"It was short trial, but GitHub Pages just works better for me.","date":"2022-06-19T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"June 19, 2022","tags":[{"label":"netlify","permalink":"/blog/tags/netlify"},{"label":"hosting","permalink":"/blog/tags/hosting"}],"readingTime":1.26,"truncated":true,"authors":[{"name":"Charles Ancheta","title":"Computer Engineering Student","url":"https://github.com/cbebe","imageURL":"https://github.com/cbebe.png","key":"cbebe"}],"frontMatter":{"title":"Bye bye Netlify","slug":"bye-bye-netlify","authors":"cbebe","tags":["netlify","hosting"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Dev Log: Boboman - Day 1","permalink":"/blog/dev-log/boboman/day1"},"nextItem":{"title":"Friendship Ended with TypeScript, now Go is My Best Friend","permalink":"/blog/2022/06/07/friendship-ended"}},"content":"It was short trial, but GitHub Pages just works better for me.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\nA couple of weeks ago, I moved my website from GitHub Pages to Netlify, hoping\\nfor a better development and production experience. I didn\'t really have a need\\nto move just yet, but I wanted to see what the buzz about Netlify was about. So\\nI spent a few hours setting it up and pointing my domain to the Netlify app.\\n\\nIt was working just fine at first, until I started making updates. The page\\nwould just load indefinitely and I would have to visit `cbebe.netlify.app`\\nfirst before `charlesancheta.com` would behave properly. I\'ve had a few\\nembarrassing moments showing my website to people for a couple times and it\\nrefusing to load.\\n\\nAnother annoying was that every pull request and push to the master branch\\nwould trigger a build, even if none of the pages were modified. Netlify only\\nprovides a limited about of build time every month, so I found myself\\ncancelling more builds in the Netlify dashboard more often than I manually\\ndeployed a build using the command line. This could be nice if other people\\nwere contributing to this repo, but since this is a personal website, I find\\nthat unlikely.\\n\\nRealizing these, I moved back to GitHub Pages and manually deploying with the\\nCLI. Maybe in the future where I would have to actually launch a\\nproduction-level static website that I would revisit Netlify, but for now, I\'ll\\nstick with my current workflow."},{"id":"/2022/06/07/friendship-ended","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/2022/06/07/friendship-ended","editUrl":"https://github.com/cbebe/charlesancheta.com/edit/master/blog/2022-06-07-friendship-ended/index.md","source":"@site/blog/2022-06-07-friendship-ended/index.md","title":"Friendship Ended with TypeScript, now Go is My Best Friend","description":"Friendship ended","date":"2022-06-07T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"June 7, 2022","tags":[{"label":"dev","permalink":"/blog/tags/dev"},{"label":"go","permalink":"/blog/tags/go"},{"label":"typescript","permalink":"/blog/tags/typescript"},{"label":"backend","permalink":"/blog/tags/backend"},{"label":"meme","permalink":"/blog/tags/meme"}],"readingTime":0.075,"truncated":true,"authors":[{"name":"Charles Ancheta","title":"Computer Engineering Student","url":"https://github.com/cbebe","imageURL":"https://github.com/cbebe.png","key":"cbebe"}],"frontMatter":{"title":"Friendship Ended with TypeScript, now Go is My Best Friend","authors":"cbebe","tags":["dev","go","typescript","backend","meme"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Bye bye Netlify","permalink":"/blog/bye-bye-netlify"},"nextItem":{"title":"TIL: My actual height","permalink":"/blog/til/my-actual-height"}},"content":"![Friendship ended](./friendship-ended.webp)\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\nNo blog post here, just a quick edit I made in GIMP."},{"id":"til/my-actual-height","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/til/my-actual-height","editUrl":"https://github.com/cbebe/charlesancheta.com/edit/master/blog/til/2022-05-29-my-actual-height/index.md","source":"@site/blog/til/2022-05-29-my-actual-height/index.md","title":"TIL: My actual height","description":"Today I learned what my actual height was (at least at the time of writing).","date":"2022-05-29T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"May 29, 2022","tags":[{"label":"til","permalink":"/blog/tags/til"}],"readingTime":0.75,"truncated":true,"authors":[{"name":"Charles Ancheta","title":"Computer Engineering Student","url":"https://github.com/cbebe","imageURL":"https://github.com/cbebe.png","key":"cbebe"}],"frontMatter":{"title":"TIL: My actual height","slug":"til/my-actual-height","authors":"cbebe","tags":["til"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Friendship Ended with TypeScript, now Go is My Best Friend","permalink":"/blog/2022/06/07/friendship-ended"},"nextItem":{"title":"Welcome!","permalink":"/blog/welcome"}},"content":"Today I learned what my actual height was (at least at the time of writing).\\nFor a few years now I\'ve always kind of just stuck with 170 cm because that\'s\\nwhat was in my driver\'s license when I got it 5 years ago (I really need to\\npass the road test this year). I\'m not even sure if that was right at the time.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\nSo, I took a couple of IKEA measuring tapes (courtesy of Jherzey), put them\\ntogether on a post in our basement, got a square ruler (triangular?\\n(\\\\*sigh\\\\*...\\n[_eskwala_](https://philnews.ph/2021/06/10/eskwala-in-english-translate-eskwala-in-english/)))\\nand measured my height.\\n\\n![A square measuring my height at 173 cm](./173cm.webp)\\n\\nSo I guess I grew 3 cm in those 5 years? I still haven\'t caught up to my dad\'s\\npeak height (176 cm), but he\'s a bit shorter now that he\'s older, so it\'s okay.\\nMy hair can add at least 2 inches :joy:."},{"id":"welcome","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/welcome","editUrl":"https://github.com/cbebe/charlesancheta.com/edit/master/blog/2022-05-28-welcome.md","source":"@site/blog/2022-05-28-welcome.md","title":"Welcome!","description":"Welcome to my website! I am Charles, a Computer Engineering Student working as","date":"2022-05-28T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"May 28, 2022","tags":[{"label":"welcome","permalink":"/blog/tags/welcome"},{"label":"first","permalink":"/blog/tags/first"}],"readingTime":0.315,"truncated":true,"authors":[{"name":"Charles Ancheta","title":"Computer Engineering Student","url":"https://github.com/cbebe","imageURL":"https://github.com/cbebe.png","key":"cbebe"}],"frontMatter":{"title":"Welcome!","slug":"welcome","authors":"cbebe","tags":["welcome","first"]},"prevItem":{"title":"TIL: My actual height","permalink":"/blog/til/my-actual-height"}},"content":"Welcome to my website! I am Charles, a Computer Engineering Student working as\\na Full Stack Web Developer.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\nFor someone who spends a lot of time typing in front of a computer, I write\\ndown very little of my thoughts. Most stuff that I come back to for memories\\nare just old code and old pictures, and this should hopefully change that."}]}')}}]);